P. Hybrids have always been at the top of the pvp ladder at the upper levels, I'm sure this is something you *should* know if you looked into the matter a bit more.<br>
<br>
I hate to say this, but dueling, not pvp, is the true test of class balance (not skill, not tactics, but what two classes can do to each other when both are ready to fight). It seems you are merely forming your opinion on Rangers based on some of the complaints, while ignoring what the class truly can do. <br>
<br>
I don't know if you are doing this to merely defend your own stance on the issue or you honestly believe it is the case, but allow me to assure you, and anyone skilled in pvp would agree, that ANY melee/hybrid class with double attack, 2h weapon skill of any type, a few almost unresistable dots, DS, and self healing most certainly does NOT suck in pvp.<br>
<br>
Claiming the opinion of a pvp ranger saying their class sucks is more valid than mine is understanble, if illogical when you bother to look at the abilities of the class. Of course you wouldn't know my personal pvp experiences, but at least you *should* know what makes a class dangerous in PvP. As someone who played a level 60 of every single class in existance except beastlord and participate in duels regularly, I can assure you the Ranger class is dangerous, even WITHOUT AM3 and EQ. <br>
<br>
Now, you can argue that I have not delt with the intricacies of PvP, and I would have to agree. I am not constantly alert. However, in the end pvp comes down to two people going head to head trying to kill the other person by any means availible be it insta-clicks, potions, charged items, etc. You cannot deny the actual fighting experiences of someone from a blue server simply because they only prepare for a fight when challenged to a duel.<br>
<br>
I see you've given up on defending your position on justifying an unbalanced skill in pvp with possible future expansions and hypothetical improvements over gear for one class. I am dissapointed that you are unable to concede that it was most illogical, and a mistake, to assume the stance in the first place, but I suppose it is up to you. <p><BR>
