<br>
Lady D's arguement was Rangers sucked before Luclin, which includes Velius, and I think both of us can agree that they did not indeed suck in Velius.<br>
<br>
I think you'd agree that the pvp game before and after Velius is completely different. Before Kunark ALL melees sucked. Kunark made melees and hybrids suck less than they did pre-Kunark. Velius made melees and hybrids far more powerful in pvp with the introduction of great weapons, especially an extremely large selection of great 2h weapons for jousting.<br>
<br>
Luclin gave rangers God status provided they have enough AA. However, a velius equipped ranger with a good 2h weapon is pretty formitable in pvp even without a bow.<br>
<br>
Yeah, I have no experience with getting jumped by 2-3 players, but if Lady D was basing her statement of "rangers sucked before Luclin" on how little rangers can do against 2-3 people who jump them... then that begs the question what other classes can do when 2-3 players jump them? Rangers can't gate, that's about it.<br>
<br>
As for clerics, the resist reduction on their nukes, especially Judgement, is far more than I expected. A few weeks ago I put on my normal resist gear and tested it with a 60 cleric. With 255 MR I did not resist a single Judgement from him, 80% landed for 500+.<br>
<br>
Yes, cast time is still an issue, and nobody's going to expect clerics to suddenly go around killing everyone, but they've got a pretty decent upgrade if you add in the new focus items. <p><BR>
