<br>
Wrong.<br>
<br>
You are knowledgable about one aspect of pvp under one set of circumstances.<br>
<br>
&quot;I hate to say this, but dueling, not pvp, is the true test of class balance &quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;...what two classes can do to each other when both are ready to fight&quot;<br>
<br>
Way wrong.  class balance can be defined as what the class is capable of in all environments under all sorts of circumstances. The sum of all this types of experience is a description of how powerful a class is.  The problem with declaring duels to be THE description of class balance is that situations will occur way way way more often than not that are far and away nothing like a duel especially as multiple parties on both sides and mobs become involved.<br>
<br>
If you balance classes based on what is in fact only a fraction of pvp, that is 1 on 1 fights in a fair enviroment with no interferance in which both parties are totally prepared then what happens in the majority of fights which don't follow that template?  Factors you didn't plan on come into play and your &quot;balance&quot; is fubar and meaningless.<br>
<br>
Take poison as an example.  In a duel vs a real pvper whose prepared its not very strong.  Just put on some pr gear and slap a pr buff on.  In a real fight at least on RZ it's very useful because most don't run around with good pr all the time.<br>
<br>
Do you balance classes based on poison being useless or good? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uboinshar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Boinshar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/18/02 1:56:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub175.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=681.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dusted.net/pstgif.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: My closing arguement</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
