<br>
I will attempt to use capitalization to capture your attention.<br>
<br>
When you speak of CLASS balance in PvP, I would assume <br>
even you would understand that CLASS balance has nothing to do with PLAYER skill. If you still don't get it, read it a few times, distinguish between CLASS and PLAYER, and read it a few more times until you get it.<br>
<br>
The viability of a CLASS changes in the hands of players. However, you cannot say a CLASS is not viable just because it's being played by an inexperienced player. Therefore, the only way to determine CLASS viability, is in a controlled environment uneffected by PLAYER skill.<br>
<br>
If you still don't understand, here's some more obvious things you appear to be missing. Anticipation is a PLAYER trait. Reaction is a PLAYER trait. Calling in help from friends is a PLAYER trait. Using the terrain to lose your enemy, or to dodge arrows is a PLAYER trait. Prepertation is a PLAYER trait. Knowing when to run is a PLAYER trait. They have absolutely nothing to do with the class you play. Therefore, they should not be considered when you speak of CLASS viability.<br>
<br>
My statement stands, the dueling aspect of PvP is the best representation of CLASS viability assuming the participants are equally skilled players.<br>
